    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A genre of artmaking practice that exhibits any of various performative or theatrical aspects, with or without the artist's physical presence. Generally considered to be temporal, works within this genre may also be object-oriented, but incorporate a sense of time, situation, process, bodily presence, or theatricality, and that break down barriers between the plastic arts and traditional forms of theater or spectacle.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000106487/Petersen and Atkinson. Installation Art: Between Image and Stage (2015)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gênero de prática artística que exibe vários aspectos performativos ou teatrais, com ou sem a presença física do artista. Geralmente consideradas temporais, as obras deste género também podem ser orientadas para o objecto, mas incorporam um sentido de tempo, situação, processo, presença corporal ou teatralidade, e que quebram barreiras entre as artes plásticas e as formas tradicionais de teatro ou espectáculo.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
